{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unwanted SMS and MMS messages are a persistent, frustrating nuisance. Identity Lookup is a new framework that allows you to participate in the process of filtering incoming messages. Get the details of how to identify and prevent these unsolicited messages. Understand the options for on-device detection as well as more dynamic server-based integration in order to ensure a better user experience."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-702-Privacy-and-Your-Apps"],"type":"links","style":"list"}]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/249","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (17 min)"}},"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-249-filtering-unwanted-messages-with-identity-lookup"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC17","title":"Filtering Unwanted Messages with Identity Lookup","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-249-Filtering-Unwanted-Messages-with-Identity-Lookup","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-212-whats-new-in-foundation","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-212-Whats-New-in-Foundation","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Whether you’re building apps for iOS, macOS, watchOS, or tvOS, a lot of the functionality you get from Apple’s SDKs comes from the Foundation framework. Join the Foundation engineering team to hear about the improvements they’ve been working on. Learn how significant changes to key paths can help make your code safer with strong type checking in Swift. Hear all about how the new archiving API can help you safely convert your native Swift types to and from external formats like JSON.  Gain insights into performance enhancements that will help make your app even more efficient.","type":"text"}],"title":"What’s New in Foundation","type":"topic"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}]},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-702-Privacy-and-Your-Apps":{"title":"Privacy and Your Apps","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-702-privacy-and-your-apps","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-702-Privacy-and-Your-Apps","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Protecting user privacy is a core principal in the Apple ecosystem. Learn what that means for the way you design and implement your apps, and learn about privacy-related changes, including new APIs, in the next versions of iOS, macOS, watchOS and tvOS.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"title":"Learn More…"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2017/249":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/249","type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/249","checksum":null}}}